# =============================================================================
#  config/suppressions.list — Silence known-acceptable findings
#
#  One finding title substring per line.
#  Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
#  How to use:
#    1. Run CHASE and review the JSON report.
#    2. Find a finding you have acknowledged/accepted.
#    3. Copy a unique substring of its "title" field here.
#    4. CHASE will skip that finding on future scans.
#
#  Example suppressions (uncomment to activate):
# =============================================================================

# CRYPTO-openssl-not-available
# IAM service-account-interactive-shell-backup
# Filesystem world-writable file: /opt/app/logs
